TextChange: Everywhere we look - from stores, to tv commercials, to items in our friends' houses - an item's \"image\" is seen. Often it is from that a company would like us to interpret it as \"favorable.\" Our impressions of people, both known and unknown, are also often based on an image. When looking deeper however, it can be seen that images don't always represent reality. In fact, images are often an illusion, one that is created simply to trick out minds into believing something is great when it actually, really, is just the opposite. => W
